Dependencies:
        * Python3 dependencies (installed via pip):
                1. scikit-commpy
                2. matplotlib

How to run:
        * Run the corresponding files for each of the modulation scheme
                $ python3 <file>.py

Tested on:
        * Linux kernel version: 6.1.12-arch1-1
        * Python version: 3.10.9

Note that all the plots are stored in the "plots" directory

References:
        * https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/complex-numbers-in-python-set-1-introduction/
        * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/62983674/the-absolute-value-of-a-complex-number-with-numpy
        * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/55700338/how-to-generate-a-complex-gaussian-white-noise-signal-in-pythonor-numpy-scipy
